        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3219027645" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1826423095653973829">Came across a review of this Dr. Seuss book that I had never seen before. I didn&apos;t expect to find an unfamiliar Dr. Seuss, so I took a few moments (which was all I had to spare) and read it. It is an early work and Seusslike, but more in the form or a traditional fairytale than his books usually are. What&apos;s not to enjoy if Theodore is involved? I have loved every word he has put to paper.<br/><br/>So, a bit of fun in an otherwise not much fun day.</span>
  <span id="freeText1826423095653973829" style="display:none">Came across a review of this Dr. Seuss book that I had never seen before. I didn't expect to find an unfamiliar Dr. Seuss, so I took a few moments (which was all I had to spare) and read it. It is an early work and Seusslike, but more in the form or a traditional fairytale than his books usually are. What's not to enjoy if Theodore is involved? I have loved every word he has put to paper.<br /><br />So, a bit of fun in an otherwise not much fun day.</span>
