<span id="freeTextContainer3275953755957697545">Fun! I may have read this one when I was young, but I didn&apos;t remember most of the details - except maybe when the hats started getting fancier with each one. I seemed to remember that.<br/><br/>I wanted an explanation for why Bartholomew suddenly couldn&apos;t take off his hat, but I did like that it was brought up again in the end, that no one &quot;could ever explain how the strange thing had happened. They only could say it just &apos;happened to happen&apos; and was not very likely to happen again.&quot; <br/><br/>This is one of the lo</span>
  <span id="freeText3275953755957697545" style="display:none">Fun! I may have read this one when I was young, but I didn't remember most of the details - except maybe when the hats started getting fancier with each one. I seemed to remember that.<br /><br />I wanted an explanation for why Bartholomew suddenly couldn't take off his hat, but I did like that it was brought up again in the end, that no one "could ever explain how the strange thing had happened. They only could say it just 'happened to happen' and was not very likely to happen again." <br /><br />This is one of the longer Dr. Seuss books. It isn't for beginning readers. It also doesn't have his trademark rhyming text. Still, a fun story and well worth reading.</span>
